2.  **`onCreateView` Method**:
    *   This method is responsible for inflating the fragment's UI. It calls `r4.inflate(com.huawei.module_checkout.R$layout.fragment_pay_discount, r5, r0)`, loading the layout `fragment_pay_discount`.
    *   It then proceeds to locate specific UI elements within the inflated view using `androidx.viewbinding.ViewBindings.findChildViewById`. The elements targeted are identified by their resource IDs: `com.huawei.module_checkout.R$id.iv_back` (an `ImageView`), `com.huawei.module_checkout.R$id.lb_next` (a `LoadingButton`), `com.huawei.module_checkout.R$id.rv_list` (a `RecyclerView`), and `com.huawei.module_checkout.R$id.tv_title` (a `TextView`).
